{"ID":270264, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"264\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs263.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs265.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 264<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">unto them that believe;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and also informs us that life and immortality were brought to light through\n  the gospel;<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> that the scripture, as Paul said to the Galatians, foreseeing that God would justify the\n  heathen through faith, preached before the gospel unto Abraham: saying, In thee shall all nations\n  be blessed.<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Gospel Always the Same<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Now taking it for granted that the scriptures say what they mean, and mean what they say, we\n  have sufficient grounds to go on and prove from the Bible that the gospel has always been the same;<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span>\n  the ordinances to fulfill its requirements, the same, and the officers to officiate, the same;<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and the\n  signs and fruits resulting from the promises, the same: therefore, as Noah was a preacher of\n  righteousness<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> he must have been baptized and ordained to the priesthood by the laying on of the\n  hands,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> etc. For no man taketh this honor unto himself except he be called of God as was Aaron,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span>\n  and Aaron was baptized in the cloud and in the sea, together with all Israel, as is related by the\n  Apostle in Corinthians.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> This position or fact, is witnessed in this manner: the covenant of\n  circumcision made with Abraham,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and practiced steadily up to the departing of Israel out of Egypt,\n  was abandoned in the wilderness, forty years&mdash;and renewed by Joshua after he passed over Jordan,\n  and encamped at Gilgal, where he made sharp knives and circumcised the whole male portion of the\n  church.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"wideEllipse\">* * *<\/p>\n\n  <div class=\"topic \">Man Must Be Born Again<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Nicodemus came to Jesus by night, and said unto him, Rabbi, we know that thou art a teacher\n  come from God: for no man can do these miracles that thou doest, except God be with him. Jesus\n  answered and said unto him, Verily, verily, I say unto thee, Except a man be born again he cannot\n  see the kingdom of God. Nicodemus saith unto him, How can a man be born when he is old? can\n  he enter the second time into his mother&rsquo;s womb, and be born?&mdash;Jesus answered, Verily, verily, I\n  say unto thee, Except a man be born of water, and of the Spirit, he cannot enter into the kingdom of\n  God.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> This strong and positive answer of Jesus, as to water baptism,<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> settles the question: If God\n  is the same yesterday, today, and forever:<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> it<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109227\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109227)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109227)\">Rom. 1:16<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110037\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110037)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110037)\">2 Tim. 1:10<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109731\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109731)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109731)\">Gal. 3:8<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110336\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110336)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110336)\">Heb. 13:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111303\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111303)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111303)\">2 Ne. 29:9<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113024\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113024)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113024)\">Moro. 10:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113343\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113343)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113343)\">D&amp;C 20:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110221\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110221)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110221)\">Heb. 7:24<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110550\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110550)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110550)\">2 Pet. 2:5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115488\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115488)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115488)\">D&amp;C 107:52<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116956\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116956)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116956)\">Moses 8:19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110151\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110151)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110151)\">Heb. 5:4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109493\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109493)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109493)\">1 Cor. 10:1-2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106028\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106028)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106028)\">Gen. 17:9-10<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106359\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106359)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106359)\">Josh. 5:2-7<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108636\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108636)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108636)\">John 3:1-5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">13. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111324\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111324)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111324)\">2 Ne. 31:13-14,17<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113686\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113686)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113686)\">D&amp;C 39:6<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116143\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116143)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116143)\">D&amp;C 128:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">14. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110337\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110337)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110337)\">Heb. 13:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"124514\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 124514)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(124514)\">1 Ne. 10:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"124515\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 124515)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(124515)\">2 Ne. 2:4<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"124516\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 124516)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(124516)\">Morm. 9:9<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113344\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113344)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113344)\">D&amp;C 20:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}